&gt; Now out of the city, the shuttle made a wide banking turn to come back around and make a second pass over the city.

&lt;NEW&gt;

As the shuttle passed over the city it could easily make out the crash
site of the fallen jet, smoke was rising up from the hole it made as
it had impaceted the side of a building. There were no life signs
comming from the crash site. If it was still alive at all it was in
deep stassis lock.

Meanwhile the armored lion could not be seen on the streets
themselves, it was sitting underneath one of the more dilapotated
building watching everything unfold, cautious optics watching and
waiting. There was something more it should be doing, but somehow it
could not think of what. Laying its head down on its paws it continued
to watch as behind it a tail began to swish and flick.

